-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Module REQ_SEC_01 models detection and flagging of suspicious withdrawal patterns using permissions, actors, resources, interfaces, and states.
-- Summary 2: Fixed type mismatches: channel comparisons now use Interface sig, target checks use concrete TransactionDatabaseResource.
-- Summary 3: Resolved contradictory facts by removing nfr_fact_performance_latency and nfr_fact_maintainability_no_circular.
-- Summary 4: Added concrete Resource TransactionDatabaseResource to enable meaningful suspicious withdrawal detection.
-- Summary 5: Corrected is_suspicious_withdrawal predicate to use TransactionDatabaseResource and proper owner check.
-- Summary 6: Adjusted acceptance criterion and test scenario predicates to align with corrected types.
-- Summary 7: All assertions and run commands should be satisfiable with the revised facts.
-- Assumption 1: TransactionDatabaseResource is owned by Operations_Team.
-- Assumption 2: Suspicious withdrawal is modeled by Write permission on transaction database resource with non-owner initiator.
-- Assumption 3: Unusual amounts are represented by Admin permission.
-- Assumption 4: Flagging for review is indicated by post-state Post1.
-- Open issue 1: Edge case 3 assertion (ec_safe_3) requires all channels authenticated, which may conflict with inv_authenticated_channel_required (only at least one). Could be relaxed in future.
-- Open issue 2: No explicit modeling of rapid successive withdrawals beyond single operation; concurrency is represented by different op instances.
-- Open issue 3: Non-functional requirement proxies are simplified and may not fully capture performance or availability.


